<h3>Allowing new item creation</h3>
<p>You can allow users to add a new item when no match is found by specifying an action for <code>on-add</code>. The typed text gets sent with the action as a parameter. You will need to handle updating the content array and the current selection on your own. You can also customize the "Add " text with the <code>addLabel</code> option.</p>
<br>
  <div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6">
    {{code-snippet name="add-new.hbs"}}

    {{code-snippet name="add-new.js"}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">

  {{!-- BEGIN-SNIPPET add-new --}}
  {{searchable-select
    content=talkTags
    sortBy="name"
    optionLabelKey="tag"
    canAddNew=true
    selected=selectedTag
    on-add=(action "addNew")}}

  {{!-- END-SNIPPET --}}

  </div>
</div>